AvatarSet(address,address).details: Emitted each time the avatar is set.

Initialized(uint8).details: Triggered when the contract has been initialized or reinitialized.

TargetSet(address,address).details: Emitted each time the Target is set.

params._controllers: addresses to add to the contoller list

params.execTxData: data of the transaction to execute

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._controllers: addresses to remove from the controller list

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAvatar(address).details: Sets the avatar to a new avatar (`newAvatar`).

setGuard(address).details: Set a guard that checks transactions before execution.

params._guard: The address of the guard to be used or the 0 address to disable the guard.

setTarget(address).details: Sets the target to a new target (`newTarget`).

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addControllers(address[]).notice: Adds `_controllers` to the list of controllers, which are allowed to execute transactions on the Safe.

controllers(address).notice: Mapping of whether an address is a controller (typically a parentDAO).

execTx(bytes).notice: Allows an authorized address to execute arbitrary transactions on the Safe.

removeControllers(address[]).notice: Removes `_controllers` from the list of controllers.

userdoc.notice: Implementation of [IFractalModule](./interfaces/IFractalModule.md). A Safe module contract that allows for a "parent-child" DAO relationship. Adding the module allows for a designated set of addresses to execute transactions on the Safe, which in our implementation is the set of parent DAOs.
